# Discussion Notes

## Why I Built This Project

I wanted to explore how unreliable operational datasets can impact analytics and AI workflows.

The goal was to create a simple validation system capable of:

- Detecting invalid records
- Improving data quality
- Producing structured diagnostic reporting
- Separating validation logic from the UI layer

## Key Design Decisions

### Modular Validation

Validation logic was separated into reusable functions to support future reuse in:

- APIs
- Containers
- Streaming systems
- Cloud or edge deployments

### Streamlit Dashboard

The dashboard provides:

- Data visibility
- Quality metrics
- Validation summaries
- CSV export functionality

## Scalability Direction

The current implementation processes static CSV files.

Possible future evolution:

- Live sensor ingestion
- Kafka or MQTT streams
- Distributed validation workers
- Cloud deployment pipelines

## Docker Approach

Docker allows the project to:

- Run consistently across environments
- Simplify deployment
- Support cloud or edge portability

## Reliability Approach

Reliability is improved through:

- Automated tests
- Structured validation rules
- Consistent reporting
- Reusable modular logic

## Current Focus

Currently improving:

- Deployment understanding
- Streaming validation concepts
- Infrastructure thinking
- Automated testing workflows
